comments: Brown (BKN) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs when he brushes Portis' (MIL) arm as Portis secures the rebound.
Brown (BKN) slightly extends his arms and marginal contact occurs with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) back, which does not affect Antetokounmpo's ability to tap out the rebound.
Portis (MIL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes contact to Brown's (BKN) wrist and affects his putback dunk attempt.
Holiday (MIL) swipes down and makes contact with Drummond's (BKN) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
Curry (BKN) is trailing Holiday (MIL) when he extends his leg into his path and makes foot to foot contact, which affects Holiday's SQBR at the end of the drive.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Durant (BKN) engage and disengage off-ball and marginal contact occurs. which does not affect Durant's ability to get to the pass.
Durant (BKN) is in the paint for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Holiday (MIL) extends out in his attempt to deflect Irving's (BKN) pass and incidental foot to foot contact occurs after the release, which does not affect Irving's ability to make his intended pass.
Brown (BKN) pushes Antetokounmpo (MIL) into Durant (BKN) during the screen.
Drummond (BKN) legally contests Antetokounmpo's (MIL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Mills (BKN) and Dragic (BKN) both establish themselves in Matthews' (MIL) path and absorb the contact during the double screen.
Matthews (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position in Durant's (BKN) path and avoids contact with his arm during the drive.
Durant (BKN) switches his pivot foot prior to the shot attempt.
Matthews (MIL) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Hill (MIL) engages with Dragic (BKN), who falls to the floor but is not dislodged from his rebounding position by the contact with Hill.
Durant (BKN) makes marginal contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) non-shooting arm as he extends it during his shooting motion.
Curry (BKN) is positioned inside of the three-point arc before Antetokounmpo (MIL) releases his free throw attempt.
Curry (BKN) briefly places a hand on Holiday's (MIL) front and marginal contact occurs as Holiday temporarily loses control of his dribble during the drive.
Portis (MIL) initiates the marginal contact as he mutually engages and disengages with Dragic (BKN) during the rebound.
Allen (MIL) swipes down and makes contact with Claxton's (BKN) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
Dragic (BKN) briefly grasps and immediately releases Allen's (MIL) jersey during the screen, which does not affect his FOM and ability to cut to the perimeter.
Curry (BKN) dislodges Matthews (MIL) from his legally obtained rebounding position.
During the rebound, Holiday (MIL) and Irving (BKN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Matthews (MIL) makes clean ball contact to deflect the pass away from Irving (BKN).

Replay review of the foul called on Matthews (MIL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Matthews (MIL) closes out on Durant (BKN) and makes contact to his lower body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) brings his arm down and makes contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Matthews (MIL) and Durant (BKN) engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his ability to get to the inbounds pass.
Matthews (MIL) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
